# MONOREPO STRUCTURE
Our project is divided into three main environments. Never mix Astro code with ESP32 C++ code.

## 1. /core/sentry (C++ / PlatformIO)
**Hardware:** ESP32 #1, PZEM-004T, 5V Relay, Hi-Link Power Supply.
**Goal:** Read AC mains data every 500ms. If Watts > 2500, turn Relay OFF. Broadcast struct via ESP-NOW to Avatar MAC Address.

## 2. /core/avatar (C++ / PlatformIO)
**Hardware:** ESP32 #2, 1.3" I2C OLED (SH1106), 12-Bit NeoPixel, KY-040 Encoder.
**Goal:** Receive ESP-NOW struct. Update Emotive State. Draw RoboEyes on OLED. Send HTTPS POST packet with JSON data to the Astro backend API endpoint every 10 seconds.

## 3. /dashboard (Astro + React + Tailwind + MongoDB)
**Goal:** A dark-mode UI(rest explained in the instructions), that acts as both the Frontend and the Backend.
**Backend (Astro API Endpoints):** - Exposes an endpoint (e.g., `/api/log-energy`) to receive POST requests from the Avatar ESP32.
- Uses `mongoose` to securely save this data directly into **MongoDB Atlas**.
**Frontend:** - Uses ReactBits for backgrounds, Tabler Icons, Recharts for graphing power flux.
- Fetches historical data directly from MongoDB. 
- Uses Gemini AI API to analyze MongoDB data and generate "Emotive Advice".